data.name: checkBoxCBuseCB.ToolTip
data.value: Enables copying all text from the program to the clipboard.

data.name: checkBoxCBIgnoreTags.ToolTip
data.value: Some games will use html style <> tags for graphics, which can fill up the clipboard. This removes those tags. Note some games use <> in normal text.

data.name: label29.ToolTip
data.value: If the Ignore <> tags setting is enabled, this will replace <> sets with another text string. Useful for creating a little space between text blocks that previously had graphics from <> tags between them.

data.name: textBoxCBReplaceTags.ToolTip
data.value: If the Ignore <> tags setting is enabled, this will replace <> sets with another text string. Useful for creating a little space between text blocks that previously had graphics from <> tags between them.

data.name: checkBoxCBNewLinesOnly.Text
data.value: Show new lines only - Classic Mode

data.name: checkBoxCBNewLinesOnly.ToolTip
data.value: Classic mode only sends lines to the clipboard that weren't previously sent there. If disabled, it instead uses the "Lines to send to Clipboard" setting to determine how many of the newest lines to send and will resend old lines to fill that amount.

data.name: checkBoxCBClearBuffer.Text
data.value: Clear Clipboard and Buffer when game screen clears

data.name: checkBoxCBClearBuffer.ToolTip
data.value: This will clear the clipboard and buffers whenever the game explicitly clears the whole screen. Otherwise it merely inserts a blank line and keeps all text.

data.name: label27.ToolTip
data.value: Triggers are what causes the clipboard to update. Important for Classic Mode, which only displays the new lines since last update, and can skip text when there's too many triggers in succession.

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerLeftClick.ToolTip
data.value: This triggers on any single or double left click in the text window.

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerMiddleClick.ToolTip
data.value: This triggers on any middle click in the text window.

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerDoubleLeftClick.ToolTip
data.value: This triggers on any double left click in the text window.

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerAnyKeyWait.Text
data.value: AnyKey Wait - When the script waits for any key press

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerAnyKeyWait.ToolTip
data.value: This triggers any time the game waits for any key to be pressed. Note that this will still occur if you hold right click through a section of text.

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerInputWait.Text
data.value: Input Wait - When the script waits for user input

data.name: checkBoxCBTriggerInputWait.ToolTip
data.value: This trigger occurs any time the program asks for text input.

data.name: numericUpDownCBMaxCB.ToolTip

data.name: numericUpDownCBBufferSize.ToolTip
